        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 19 at 4:24PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 424 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Southside in Independence County, or 8 miles south of Batesville,
moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Batesville...                     Newark...
Pleasant Plains...                Oil Trough...
Concord...                        Magness...
Salado...                         Southside in Independence Count...
Almond...                         Thida...
Rosie...                          Desha...
Locust Grove...                   Huff...
Hutchinson...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
